<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Kings 2:1-46</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="22">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="46">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And the days of David gradually drew near for him to die; and he proceeded to command Sol&acute;o&middot;mon his son, saying:</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">“I am going in the way of all the earth, and you must be strong and prove yourself to be a man.</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">And you must keep the obligation to Jehovah your God by walking in his ways, by keeping his statutes, his commandments and his judicial decisions and his testimonies, according to what is written in the law of Moses, in order that you may act prudently in everything that you do and everywhere that you turn;</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">in order that Jehovah may carry out his word that he spoke respecting me, saying, ‘If your sons will take care of their way by walking before me in truth with all their heart and with all their soul, there will not be cut off a man of yours from [sitting] upon the throne of Israel.’</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">“And you yourself also well know what Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah did to me in what he did to two chiefs of the armies of Israel, to Ab&acute;ner the son of Ner and A&middot;ma&acute;sa the son of Je&acute;ther, when he killed them and placed the blood of war in peacetime and put the blood of war on his belt that was about his hips and in his sandals that were on his feet.</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And you must act according to your wisdom, and not let his gray hairs go down in peace to She&acute;ol.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">“And toward the sons of Bar&middot;zil&acute;lai the Gil&acute;e&middot;ad&middot;ite you should exercise loving-kindness, and they must prove to be among those eating at your table; for that was the way they drew near to me when I ran away from before Ab&acute;sa&middot;lom your brother.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">“And here there is with you Shim&acute;e&middot;i the son of Ge&acute;ra the Ben&acute;ja&middot;min&middot;ite from Ba&middot;hu&acute;rim, and he it was that called down evil upon me with a painful malediction on the day that I was going to Ma&middot;ha&middot;na&acute;im; and he it was that came down to meet me at the Jordan, so that I swore to him by Jehovah, saying, ‘I shall not put you to death by the sword.’</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">And now do not leave him unpunished, for you are a wise man and you well know what you ought to do to him, and you must bring his gray hairs down to She&acute;ol with blood.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">Then David lay down with his forefathers and was buried in the City of David.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And the days that David had reigned over Israel were forty years. In He&acute;bron he had reigned seven years, and in Jerusalem he had reigned thirty-three years.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">As for Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, he sat down upon the throne of David his father; and gradually his kingship became very firmly established.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">In time Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah the son of Hag&acute;gith came to Bath-she&acute;ba, Sol&acute;o&middot;mon’s mother. At this she said: “Is your coming peaceable?” to which he said: “It is peaceable.”</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And he went on to say: “There is a matter I have for you.” So she said: “Speak.”</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And he continued: “You yourself well know that the kingship was to have become mine, and it was toward me that all Israel had set their face for me to become king; but the kingship turned and came to be my brother’s, for it was from Jehovah that it became his.</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">And now there is one request that I am making of you. Do not turn my face away.” Accordingly she said to him: “Speak.”</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And he went on to say: “Please, say to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon the king (for he will not turn your face away) that he should give me Ab&acute;i&middot;shag the Shu&acute;nam&middot;mite as a wife.”</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">To this Bath-she&acute;ba said: “Good! I myself shall speak for you to the king.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">So Bath-she&acute;ba came in to King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon to speak to him for Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah. At once the king rose to meet her and bowed down to her. Then he sat down upon his throne and had a throne set for the mother of the king, that she might sit at his right.</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And she proceeded to say: “There is one little request that I am making of you. Do not turn my face away.” So the king said to her: “Make it, my mother; for I shall not turn your face away.”</span> <a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">And she went on to say: “Let Ab&acute;i&middot;shag the Shu&acute;nam&middot;mite be given to Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah your brother as a wife.”</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">At this King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon answered and said to his mother: “And why are you requesting Ab&acute;i&middot;shag the Shu&acute;nam&middot;mite for Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah? Request also for him the kingship (because he is my brother older than I am), even for him and for A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar the priest and for Jo&acute;ab the son of Ze&middot;ru&acute;iah.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">With that King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon swore by Jehovah, saying: “So may God do to me, and so may he add to it, if it was not against his own soul that Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah spoke this thing.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And now, as Jehovah is living who has firmly established me and keeps me seated upon the throne of David my father and who made a house for me just as he has spoken, today Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah will be put to death.”</span> <a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">Immediately King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon sent by means of Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da; and he proceeded to fall upon him, so that he died.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">And to A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar the priest the king said: “Go to An&acute;a&middot;thoth to your fields! For you are deserving of death; but on this day I shall not put you to death, because you carried the ark of the Sovereign Lord Jehovah before David my father, and because you suffered affliction during all the time that my father suffered affliction.”</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">So Sol&acute;o&middot;mon drove out A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar from serving as a priest of Jehovah, to fulfill Jehovah’s word that he had spoken against the house of E&acute;li in Shi&acute;loh.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And the report itself came clear to Jo&acute;ab—for Jo&acute;ab himself had inclined to follow Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;jah, although Ab&acute;sa&middot;lom he had not inclined to follow—and Jo&acute;ab went fleeing to the tent of Jehovah and began to hold fast to the horns of the altar.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">Then King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon was told: “Jo&acute;ab has fled to the tent of Jehovah, and there he is beside the altar.” So Sol&acute;o&middot;mon sent Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da, saying: “Go, fall upon him!”</span> <a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">Accordingly Be&middot;nai&acute;ah came to the tent of Jehovah and said to him: “This is what the king has said, ‘Come on out!’” But he said: “No! For here is where I shall die.” At that Be&middot;nai&acute;ah brought word back to the king, saying: “This is what Jo&acute;ab spoke, and this is what he answered me.”</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">Then the king said to him: “Do just as he has spoken and fall upon him; and you must bury him and remove from off me and from off the house of my father the blood undeservedly shed that Jo&acute;ab spilled.</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And Jehovah will certainly bring back his blood upon his own head, because he fell upon two men more righteous and better than he was, and he proceeded to kill them with the sword, when my father David himself had not known of it, namely, Ab&acute;ner the son of Ner the chief of the army of Israel and A&middot;ma&acute;sa the son of Je&acute;ther the chief of the army of Judah.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">And their blood must come back upon the head of Jo&acute;ab and upon the head of his offspring to time indefinite; but for David and for his offspring and for his house and for his throne there will come to be peace to time indefinite from Jehovah.”</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">Then Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da went on up and fell upon him and put him to death; and he got to be buried at his own house in the wilderness.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Upon that the king put Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da in place of him over the army; and Za&acute;dok the priest the king put in the place of A&middot;bi&acute;a&middot;thar.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">Finally the king sent and called Shim&acute;e&middot;i and said to him: “Build yourself a house in Jerusalem, and you must dwell there and not go out from there to this place and that.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">And it must occur that on the day of your going out and when you do pass over the torrent valley of Kid&acute;ron, you should unmistakably know that you will positively die. Bloodguilt for you will itself come to be upon your own head.”</span> <a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">At this Shim&acute;e&middot;i said to the king: “The word is good. Just as my lord the king has spoken is the way that your servant will do.” And Shim&acute;e&middot;i kept dwelling in Jerusalem many days.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">And it came about at the end of three years that two slaves of Shim&acute;e&middot;i went running away to A&acute;chish the son of Ma&acute;a&middot;cah the king of Gath; and people came telling Shim&acute;e&middot;i, saying: “Look! Your slaves are at Gath.”</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">Immediately Shim&acute;e&middot;i got up and saddled his ass and went to Gath to A&acute;chish to look for his slaves; after which Shim&acute;e&middot;i went and brought his slaves from Gath.</span> <a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">Then Sol&acute;o&middot;mon was told: “Shim&acute;e&middot;i has gone out of Jerusalem to Gath and is back.”</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">At that the king sent and called Shim&acute;e&middot;i and said to him: “Did I not put you under oath by Jehovah that I might warn you, saying, ‘On the day of your going outside and when you do go here and there you should unmistakably know that you will positively die,’ and so did you not say to me, ‘Good is the word that I have heard’?</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">Why, then, did you not keep the oath of Jehovah and the commandment that I solemnly laid upon you?”</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">And the king went on to say to Shim&acute;e&middot;i: “You yourself certainly know all the injury which your heart well knows that you did to David my father; and Jehovah will certainly return the injury by you upon your own head.</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">But King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon will be blessed, and the throne of David itself will prove to be firmly established before Jehovah forever.”</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">With that the king commanded Be&middot;nai&acute;ah the son of Je&middot;hoi&acute;a&middot;da, who then went out and fell upon him, so that he died.</span>
</p>

<p> 
       <span id="vs46-2">And the kingdom was firmly established in the hand of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon.</span>
</p>
</form>

