<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Kings 5:1-18</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="22">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="18">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And Hi&acute;ram the king of Tyre proceeded to send his servants to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, for he had heard that it was he that they had anointed as king in place of his father; for a lover of David Hi&acute;ram had always proved to be.</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">In turn Sol&acute;o&middot;mon sent to Hi&acute;ram, saying:</span> <a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">“You yourself well know that David my father was not able to build a house to the name of Jehovah his God because of the warfare with which they surrounded him, until Jehovah put them under the soles of his feet.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">And now Jehovah my God has given me rest all around. There is no resister, and there is nothing bad happening.</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And here I am thinking of building a house to the name of Jehovah my God, just as Jehovah promised to David my father, saying, ‘Your son whom I shall put upon your throne in place of you, he is the one that will build the house to my name.’</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">And now command that they cut for me cedars from Leb&acute;a&middot;non; and my servants themselves will prove to be with your servants, and the wages of your servants I shall give to you according to all that you may say, for you yourself well know that there is among us no one knowing how to cut trees like the Si&middot;do&acute;ni&middot;ans.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">And it came about that as soon as Hi&acute;ram heard the words of Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, he began to rejoice greatly, and he went on to say: “Blessed is Jehovah today in that he has given David a wise son over this numerous people!”</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">Accordingly Hi&acute;ram sent to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, saying: “I have heard what you sent to me. For my part, I shall do all your delight in the matter of timbers of cedar trees and timbers of juniper trees.</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">My servants themselves will bring them down out of Leb&acute;a&middot;non to the sea; and I, for my part, shall put them in log rafts [to go] by sea clear to the place that you will send me notice of; and I shall certainly have them broken up there, and you, for your part, will carry them; and you, for your part, will do my delight by giving the food for my household.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">So Hi&acute;ram became a giver of timbers of cedar trees and timbers of juniper trees to Sol&acute;o&middot;mon according to all his delight.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, for his part, gave Hi&acute;ram twenty thousand cor measures of wheat as food supplies for his household and twenty cor measures of beaten-out oil. That was what Sol&acute;o&middot;mon kept giving Hi&acute;ram year by year.</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And Jehovah, for his part, gave Sol&acute;o&middot;mon wisdom, just as he had promised him; and there came to be peace between Hi&acute;ram and Sol&acute;o&middot;mon, and both of them proceeded to conclude a covenant.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">And King Sol&acute;o&middot;mon kept bringing up those conscripted for forced labor out of all Israel; and those conscripted for forced labor amounted to thirty thousand men.</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And he would send them to Leb&acute;a&middot;non in shifts of ten thousand a month. For a month they would continue in Leb&acute;a&middot;non, for two months at their homes; and Ad&middot;o&middot;ni&acute;ram was over those conscripted for forced labor.</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">And Sol&acute;o&middot;mon came to have seventy thousand burden bearers and eighty thousand cutters in the mountain,</span> <a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">besides Sol&acute;o&middot;mon’s princely deputies who were over the work, three thousand three hundred foremen over the people who were active in the work.</span> <a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">Accordingly the king commanded that they should quarry great stones, expensive stones, to lay the foundation of the house with hewn stones.</span> <a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">So Sol&acute;o&middot;mon’s builders and Hi&acute;ram’s builders and the Ge&acute;bal&middot;ites did the cutting, and they kept preparing the timbers and the stones to build the house.</span>
</p>
</form>

