<h1>Online Bible: New World Translation of the Holy Scriptures</h1>
</noscript>
<p class="title">1 Kings 18:1-46</p>
<form class="formtext">
<input type="hidden" name="chapterCount" value="22">
<input type="hidden" name="verseCount" value="46">
<p><a name="bk1" class="vsAnchor">1</a>
       <span id="vs1">And it came about [after] many days that Jehovah’s own word came to E&middot;li&acute;jah in the third year, saying: “Go, show yourself to A&acute;hab, as I am determined to give rain upon the surface of the ground.”</span> <a name="bk2" class="vsAnchor">2</a>
       <span id="vs2">Accordingly E&middot;li&acute;jah went to show himself to A&acute;hab, while the famine was severe in Sa&middot;mar&acute;i&middot;a.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk3" class="vsAnchor">3</a>
       <span id="vs3">Meantime, A&acute;hab called O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah, who was over the household. (Now O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah himself had proved to be one greatly fearing Jehovah.</span> <a name="bk4" class="vsAnchor">4</a>
       <span id="vs4">Hence it came about that when Jez&acute;e&middot;bel cut off Jehovah’s prophets, O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah proceeded to take a hundred prophets and keep them hid by fifties in a cave, and he supplied them bread and water.)</span> <a name="bk5" class="vsAnchor">5</a>
       <span id="vs5">And A&acute;hab went on to say to O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah: “Go through the land to all the springs of water and to all the torrent valleys. Perhaps we may find green grass, that we may preserve the horses and mules alive and may not have [any more] of the beasts cut off.”</span> <a name="bk6" class="vsAnchor">6</a>
       <span id="vs6">So they divided between themselves the land through which to pass. A&acute;hab himself went alone by one way, and O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah himself went alone by another way.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk7" class="vsAnchor">7</a>
       <span id="vs7">As O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah continued on the way, why, there was E&middot;li&acute;jah to meet him. At once he recognized him and fell upon his face and said: “Is this you, my lord E&middot;li&acute;jah?”</span> <a name="bk8" class="vsAnchor">8</a>
       <span id="vs8">At this he said to him: “It is I. Go, say to your lord, ‘Here is E&middot;li&acute;jah.’”</span> <a name="bk9" class="vsAnchor">9</a>
       <span id="vs9">But he said: “What sin have I committed that you should be putting your servant into the hand of A&acute;hab to put me to death?</span> <a name="bk10" class="vsAnchor">10</a>
       <span id="vs10">As Jehovah your God is living, there is not a nation or kingdom where my lord has not sent to look for you. After they had said, ‘He is not [here],’ he made the kingdom and the nation swear that they could not find you.</span> <a name="bk11" class="vsAnchor">11</a>
       <span id="vs11">And now you are saying, ‘Go, say to your lord: “Here is E&middot;li&acute;jah.”’</span> <a name="bk12" class="vsAnchor">12</a>
       <span id="vs12">And it is bound to occur that, when I myself go from you, then the spirit of Jehovah itself will carry you away to where I shall not know; and I shall have come to tell A&acute;hab, and he will not find you, and he will be bound to kill me, as your servant himself has feared Jehovah from his youth.</span> <a name="bk13" class="vsAnchor">13</a>
       <span id="vs13">Has not my lord been told what I did when Jez&acute;e&middot;bel killed the prophets of Jehovah, how I kept some of the prophets of Jehovah hid, a hundred men by fifties in a cave, and kept supplying them bread and water?</span> <a name="bk14" class="vsAnchor">14</a>
       <span id="vs14">And now you are saying, ‘Go, say to your lord: “Here is E&middot;li&acute;jah.”’ And he will be bound to kill me.”</span> <a name="bk15" class="vsAnchor">15</a>
       <span id="vs15">However, E&middot;li&acute;jah said: “As Jehovah of armies before whom I do stand is living, today I shall show myself to him.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk16" class="vsAnchor">16</a>
       <span id="vs16">Accordingly O&middot;ba&middot;di&acute;ah went off to meet A&acute;hab and told him; and so A&acute;hab went to meet E&middot;li&acute;jah.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk17" class="vsAnchor">17</a>
       <span id="vs17">And it came about that, as soon as A&acute;hab saw E&middot;li&acute;jah, A&acute;hab immediately said to him: “Is this you, the bringer of ostracism upon Israel?”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk18" class="vsAnchor">18</a>
       <span id="vs18">To this he said: “I have not brought ostracism upon Israel, but you and the house of your father have, because <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> men have left the commandments of Jehovah, and you went following the Ba&acute;als.</span> <a name="bk19" class="vsAnchor">19</a>
       <span id="vs19">And now send, collect together all Israel to me at Mount Car&acute;mel and also the four hundred and fifty prophets of Ba&acute;al and the four hundred prophets of the sacred pole, who are eating at the table of Jez&acute;e&middot;bel.”</span> <a name="bk20" class="vsAnchor">20</a>
       <span id="vs20">And A&acute;hab proceeded to send among all the sons of Israel and collect the prophets together at Mount Car&acute;mel.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk21" class="vsAnchor">21</a>
       <span id="vs21">Then E&middot;li&acute;jah approached all the people and said: “How long will <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> be limping upon two different opinions? If Jehovah is the [true] God, go following him; but if Ba&acute;al is, go following him.” And the people did not say a word in answer to him.</span> <a name="bk22" class="vsAnchor">22</a>
       <span id="vs22">And E&middot;li&acute;jah went on to say to the people: “I myself have been left as a prophet of Jehovah, I alone, while the prophets of Ba&acute;al are four hundred and fifty men.</span> <a name="bk23" class="vsAnchor">23</a>
       <span id="vs23">Now let them give us two young bulls, and let them choose for themselves one young bull and cut it in pieces and put it upon the wood, but they should not put fire to it. And I myself shall dress the other young bull, and I must place it upon the wood, but I shall not put fire to it.</span> <a name="bk24" class="vsAnchor">24</a>
       <span id="vs24">And <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must call upon the name of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> god, and I, for my part, shall call upon the name of Jehovah; and it must occur that the [true] God that answers by fire is the [true] God.” To this all the people answered and said: “The thing is good.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk25" class="vsAnchor">25</a>
       <span id="vs25">E&middot;li&acute;jah now said to the prophets of Ba&acute;al: “Choose for yourselves one young bull and dress it first, because <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> are the majority; and call upon the name of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> god, but <span class="smallcaps">YOU</span> must not put fire to it.”</span> <a name="bk26" class="vsAnchor">26</a>
       <span id="vs26">Accordingly they took the young bull that he gave them. Then they dressed it, and they kept calling upon the name of Ba&acute;al from morning till noon, saying: “O Ba&acute;al, answer us!” But there was no voice, and there was no one answering. And they kept limping around the altar that they had made.</span> <a name="bk27" class="vsAnchor">27</a>
       <span id="vs27">And it came about at noon that E&middot;li&acute;jah began to mock them and say: “Call at the top of <span class="smallcaps">YOUR</span> voice, for he is a god; for he must be concerned with a matter, and he has excrement and has to go to the privy. Or maybe he is asleep and ought to wake up!”</span> <a name="bk28" class="vsAnchor">28</a>
       <span id="vs28">And they began calling at the top of their voice and cutting themselves according to their custom with daggers and with lances, until they caused blood to flow out upon them.</span> <a name="bk29" class="vsAnchor">29</a>
       <span id="vs29">And it came about that, as soon as noon was past and they continued behaving as prophets until the going up of the grain offering, there was no voice, and there was no one answering, and there was no paying of attention.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk30" class="vsAnchor">30</a>
       <span id="vs30">At length E&middot;li&acute;jah said to all the people: “Approach me.” So all the people approached him. Then he proceeded to mend the altar of Jehovah that was torn down.</span> <a name="bk31" class="vsAnchor">31</a>
       <span id="vs31">So E&middot;li&acute;jah took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Jacob, to whom Jehovah’s word had come, saying: “Israel is what your name will become.”</span> <a name="bk32" class="vsAnchor">32</a>
       <span id="vs32">And he went on to build the stones into an altar in the name of Jehovah and to make a trench, of about the area sowed with two seah measures of seed, all around the altar.</span> <a name="bk33" class="vsAnchor">33</a>
       <span id="vs33">After that he put the pieces of wood in order and cut the young bull in pieces and placed it upon the pieces of wood. He now said: “F<span class="smallcaps">ILL</span> four large jars with water and pour it upon the burnt offering and upon the pieces of wood.”</span> <a name="bk34" class="vsAnchor">34</a>
       <span id="vs34">Then he said: “Do it again.” So they did it again. But he said: “Do it a third time.” So they did it a third time.</span> <a name="bk35" class="vsAnchor">35</a>
       <span id="vs35">Thus the water went all around the altar, and the trench also he filled with water.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk36" class="vsAnchor">36</a>
       <span id="vs36">And it came about at the time that the grain offering goes up that E&middot;li&acute;jah the prophet began to approach and say: “O Jehovah, the God of Abraham, Isaac and Israel, today let it be known that you are God in Israel and I am your servant and it is by your word that I have done all these things.</span> <a name="bk37" class="vsAnchor">37</a>
       <span id="vs37">Answer me, O Jehovah, answer me, that this people may know that you, Jehovah, are the [true] God and you yourself have turned their heart back.”</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk38" class="vsAnchor">38</a>
       <span id="vs38">At that the fire of Jehovah came falling and went eating up the burnt offering and the pieces of wood and the stones and the dust, and the water that was in the trench it licked up.</span> <a name="bk39" class="vsAnchor">39</a>
       <span id="vs39">When all the people saw it, they immediately fell upon their faces and said: “Jehovah is the [true] God! Jehovah is the [true] God!”</span> <a name="bk40" class="vsAnchor">40</a>
       <span id="vs40">Then E&middot;li&acute;jah said to them: “Seize the prophets of Ba&acute;al! Do not let a single one of them escape!” At once they seized them, and E&middot;li&acute;jah then brought them down to the torrent valley of Ki&acute;shon and slaughtered them there.</span>
</p>

<p><a name="bk41" class="vsAnchor">41</a>
       <span id="vs41">E&middot;li&acute;jah now said to A&acute;hab: “Go up, eat and drink; for there is the sound of the turmoil of a downpour.”</span> <a name="bk42" class="vsAnchor">42</a>
       <span id="vs42">And A&acute;hab proceeded to go up to eat and drink. As for E&middot;li&acute;jah, he went up to the top of Car&acute;mel and began crouching to the earth and keeping his face put between his knees.</span> <a name="bk43" class="vsAnchor">43</a>
       <span id="vs43">Then he said to his attendant: “Go up, please. Look in the direction of the sea.” So he went up and looked and then said: “There is nothing at all.” And he went on to say, “Go back,” for seven times.</span> <a name="bk44" class="vsAnchor">44</a>
       <span id="vs44">And it came about at the seventh time that he got to say: “Look! There is a small cloud like a man’s palm ascending out of the sea.” He now said: “Go up, say to A&acute;hab, ‘Hitch up! And go down that the downpour may not detain you!’”</span> <a name="bk45" class="vsAnchor">45</a>
       <span id="vs45">And it came about in the meantime that the heavens themselves darkened up with clouds and wind and a great downpour began to occur. And A&acute;hab kept riding and made his way to Jez&acute;re&middot;el.</span> <a name="bk46" class="vsAnchor">46</a>
       <span id="vs46">And the very hand of Jehovah proved to be upon E&middot;li&acute;jah, so that he girded up his hips and went running ahead of A&acute;hab all the way to Jez&acute;re&middot;el.</span>
</p>
</form>

